==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elicit
<hw>E*lic"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elictus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>elicere</ets> to elicit; <ets>e</ets>
+ <ets>lacere</ets> to entice. Cf. <er>Delight</er>,
<er>Lace</er>.]</ety> <def>Elicited; drawn out; made real; open;
evident.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>elicit</xex> act of
equity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elicit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Elicit
<hw>E*lic"it</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Elicited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Eliciting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To draw out or entice forth; to
bring to light; to bring out against the will; to deduce by reason or
argument; <as>as, to <ex>elicit</ex> truth by discussion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elicitate</ent>⟦br⟧
